'''Atom Technologies''' is an Indian company offering [[payment]] processing  [[technology]], headquartered in [[Mumbai]], [[India]]. atom was started in [[2006]] and is a [[subsidiary]] of the [[Financial Technologies Group]]. <ref name="business-standard.com">[http://www.business-standard.com/india/news/atom-technologies-signs-upsahayata/19/47/359326/ atom technologies signs up with Sahayata], Business Standard, May 27, 2009.
</ref>

The company has historically focused upon the distribution of [[payment]] and [[banking]] services through the use of [[mobile technology]]. atom technologies has created [[patent pending]] products & services for [[mobile payments]], Interactive Voice Response ([[IVR]]) based payments and mobile based service distribution framework. <ref name="business-standard.com"/>

atom technologies also helps [[microfinance]] [[institutions]] to expand their business through the use of effective [[Information Technology]] systems. <ref name="thehindubusinessline.com">[http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/2008/09/26/stories/2008092651940600.htm Atom Tech to offer banking via subsidiary], The Hindu Business Line, September 26, 2008.</ref>

atom is an [[acronym]] for <U+2018>'''a'''ny '''t'''ransaction '''o'''n '''m'''obile.<U+2019> <ref>[http://sify.com/finance/it-bpo/fullstory.php?id=14681834 Atom readies for a mobile big bang], Sify.com, May 27, 2008.
</ref>
==Products==

Its products include

*atom <U+2013> This is a [[Java (programming language)|Java]]/[[Java ME]] based [[mobile payment]] [[application software|application]] which enables [[consumer|consumers]] to [[payment|pay]] for services or products sold by [[merchants]] using a [[credit card]] and a [[mobile phone]].

*atom IVR <ref>[http://www.telecomtiger.com/fullstory.aspx?storyid=6502&section=S176%20 atom offers m-payment facility to IHO customers], Telecom Tiger, June 29, 2009.</ref><ref>[http://www.ciol.com/enterprise/ec-services/news-reports/goa-travel-operator-takes-the-mobile-bus/19609121280/0/ Goa Travel operator takes the Mobile bus], Ciol.com, June 19, 2009.</ref> <U+2013> This is an [[IVR]] based [[payments]] solution <ref>[http://www.business-standard.com/india/news/dialdoctorget-treated/00/01/359696/ Dial a doctor & get treated], Business Standard, June 1, 2009.</ref> which enables remote payments over the [[phone]] by punching [[credit card]] details on any [[landline]] or [[mobile phone]] [[keypad]]. <ref>[http://www.expresscomputeronline.com/20081215/management04.shtml IVR: making payments easier], Express Computer, December 15, 2008.</ref>

*atom Sewa <U+2013> This is a [[microfinance]] [[banking]] [[Platform (economics)|platform]] that enables [[bank]]s and [[microfinance]] [[institutions]] to offer on-the-spot [[cash]] [[Financial transaction|transactions]] to the [[rural]] masses. <ref name="thehindubusinessline.com"/>

==Security==

The company<U+2019>s [[payment]] platforms have been [[accredited]] for [[PCIDSS]]<ref>[http://www.mobile-financial.com/node/1071/atom-technologies atom Technologies company profile], Mobile-Financial.com</ref> & [[PA-DSS]]<ref>[http://www.ecommerce-journal.com/news/visa_certification_granted_to_india_s_m_banking_provider Visa certification granted to India<U+2019>s m-banking provider], Ecommerce Journal, August 29, 2008.</ref> [[certification]]s which are accepted by the [[banking industry]] and hence ascertain the security of its [[mobile payment]] transactions and the [[Data transmission|transmission]] of card holder data.

atom<U+2019>s [[payment]] platform uses [[Advanced Encryption Standard]] 128 [[Bit]] [[Cipher Block Chaining]] for [[routing]] [[Financial transaction|transactions]] using secure [[VPN]] connectivity. atom does not store any [[credit card]] details but acts as a pass-through to the bank<U+2019>s [[payment gateway]] for [[routing]] [[Financial transaction|transactions]].<ref>[http://www.astricon.net/topics/broadband-mobile/articles/38328-indias-atom-receives-visa-security-certification-m-payments.htm India's atom Receives VISA Security Certification for M-Payments], TMCnet.com, August 28, 2008.</ref>

==Partnerships==

atom has tie-ups with major [[bank]]s<ref>[http://in.reuters.com/article/paidmediaAtoms/idIN37053525820090604?sp=true DTH players may help mobile payments gain currency], Reuters, June 4, 2009.</ref> apart from [[credit card]] companies like [[Visa Inc.]], [[MasterCard]] and [[American Express]]. The [[credit card]]s of these [[bank]]s & companies can be used to transact on the atom platform. More than 250 [[merchants]] have tied up with atom to provide these [[payment]] services.<ref>[http://www.expresscomputeronline.com/20081215/management04.shtml IVR: making payments easier], Express Computer, December 15, 2008.</ref>

==Awards==

*atom Technologies has won "The World is Open Award 2008" for excellence in the vertical of [[financial services]].<ref>[http://www.channeltimes.com/India/News/Atom_Technologies_Wins_Red_Hat_Award/551-88568-819.html atom Technologies wins Red Hat award], April 16, 2008.</ref> This award was instituted by [[Red Hat]], in collaboration with Skoch Consultancy, to recognize the efforts being made by various industry segments such as [[banking]], [[insurance]], [[financial services]] and [[technology]].

*atom Technologies has also won the IT People Awards for Product Innovation, 2008 which was instituted by IT People Ltd. <ref>[http://www.atomtech.in/IT-people-awards.html About IT People awards], Retrieved on August 8, 2009.</ref>

*atom Technologies' m-collection model deployed at Sahayata, a [[microfinance]] [[institution]] based in [[Udaipur]], [[Rajasthan]], has received the Network Computing EDGE award in [[2009]]. <ref>[http://www.networkcomputing.in/Sahayata-EDGE-001Jun009.aspx Mobile application transforms micro-finance], Retrieved on August 8, 2009.</ref>

